text: Tsuboya ware wine bottle with spout, second Shō Dynasty, Ryukyu Kingdom, 19th century is a type of Ryukyuan pottery traditionally from Tsuboya, presently a part of Naha, in the former Ryukyu Kingdom. == External links == * http://www.tuboya.com Category:Japanese pottery Category:Naha Category:Okinawan culture
title: Tsuboya ware
